### MCP (Model Context Protocol) Endpoints
### Test file for MCP integration

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7058
# OR use HTTP
# @baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### 1. Get MCP Server Information
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/info

### 2. List Available MCP Tools
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/tools

### 3. Execute Health Check Tool
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/tools/health_check
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 4. Execute Ingest Document Tool
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/tools/ingest_document
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "mcp-test-doc",
  "title": "MCP Integration Test",
  "content": "This is a test document for MCP (Model Context Protocol) integration. It demonstrates how AI assistants can interact with the RAG system through standardized MCP tools.",
  "metadata": {
    "source": "mcp-test",
    "category": "testing",
    "author": "System"
  }
}

### 5. Execute List Documents Tool
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/tools/list_documents
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 6. Execute Search Documents Tool
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/tools/search_documents
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "MCP",
  "limit": 10
}

### 7. Execute Get Document Tool
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/tools/get_document
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "mcp-test-doc"
}

### 8. Execute Ask Question Tool
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/tools/ask_question
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is MCP?",
  "topK": 3,
  "maxAnswerSentences": 3
}

### 9. MCP JSON-RPC: Initialize
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2024-11-05",
    "clientInfo": {
      "name": "test-client",
      "version": "1.0.0"
    }
  }
}

### 10. MCP JSON-RPC: List Tools
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 2,
  "method": "tools/list"
}

### 11. MCP JSON-RPC: Call Tool (Ingest)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 3,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "ingest_document",
    "arguments": {
      "id": "jsonrpc-test",
      "title": "JSON-RPC Test Document",
      "content": "This document was ingested using the JSON-RPC MCP protocol.",
      "metadata": {
        "protocol": "json-rpc"
      }
    }
  }
}

### 12. MCP JSON-RPC: Call Tool (Ask Question)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 4,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "ask_question",
    "arguments": {
      "question": "What testing protocols are mentioned?",
      "topK": 5
    }
  }
}

### 13. Error Test: Unknown Tool
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/tools/unknown_tool
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 14. Error Test: Invalid Method (JSON-RPC)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 99,
  "method": "invalid/method"
}

### 15. Complex Question with Multiple Sources
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mcp/tools/ask_question
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "How does the system work and what are its capabilities?",
  "topK": 5,
  "maxAnswerSentences": 5
}
